    59       3.2651       4.0059       3.3673                                   
    83       3.9840       4.9541       3.7136                                   

  INTERPRETATION:
    W_1 grows with p: the eigenvalue distributions diverge
    W_2 grows even faster (concentrated vs spread = large L²)
    KL divergence captures the INFORMATION gap between distributions

    The OPTIMAL TRANSPORT MAP from Paley to Interval:
    - Takes √p/2-magnitude eigenvalues
    - Concentrates them: most mass → one large eigenvalue ~p/π
    - The transport COST = work done to concentrate the spectrum
    - This cost ≈ W_2² = Σ(|λ_j| - |μ_j|)² measures the 'effort'
    - The H-improvement is a RETURN on this spectral investment

  SPECTRAL EFFICIENCY: ΔH per unit transport cost
  (How much H improvement do you get per unit of eigenvalue rearrangement?)
  This metric could identify the OPTIMAL intermediate tournament
  on the geodesic from Paley to Interval in transport space.

